<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2814] args/result classes not found when no namespace is set</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2814</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The args/results helper classes are not found by the Haxe compiler if no namespaces are set in the IDL. With Haxe, classes are located via: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  (1) the file name matching the class name &lt;br/&gt;
  (2) wildcard &lt;tt&gt;namespace.*&lt;/tt&gt; imports. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With an empty namespace only the first method is used. Because the helper classes are located within the (e.g.) &lt;tt&gt;MethodCall_Impl.hx&lt;/tt&gt; file instead the &lt;tt&gt;MethodCall_args.hx&lt;/tt&gt; file, they are not found in that case. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Changes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;generate one source file per Haxe class&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ensure correctly capitalized names in all cases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

</description>
